title: Connections Rate (CPS) Anomaly
summary: AIOPS has detected anomalous patterns in firewall connections

analysis.detail: Cisco AIOPS has identified an anomalous pattern in firewall connections, deviating significantly from established usage trends. This unexpected behavior warrants immediate investigation to determine the root cause. Persistent occurrences may necessitate precautionary measures. If this alert is a false positive, consider reducing the anomaly detection sensitivity threshold.

probableCauses.title: NAT Translations
probableCauses.detail: AIOps observed surge in NAT Translations, it might have overloaded the Connections

remediation.markdownText:
### To troubleshoot or remediate the issue, you should:
- Check firewall logs for errors and unusual activity.
- Monitor network traffic for anomalies.
- Review firewall configuration for errors.
- Check firewall hardware and software for issues.
- Analyze network connectivity for problems.
- Review security policies to ensure they are not too permissive or restrictive.
